  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      277.63,
      95.84,
      337.4,
      109.12
    ],
    "text": "Judgement",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      118.36,
      140.3,
      131.64
    ],
    "text": "Introduction",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      154.11,
      543.22,
      167.39
    ],
    "text": "In this appeal, the Applicant-Respondent-Petitioner (hereinafter referred to as the \u201cAppellant\u201d) is",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      181.61,
      543.23,
      194.89
    ],
    "text": "married to the Respondent-Petitioner-Respondent (hereinafter referred to as the \u201cRespondent\u201d).",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      209.14,
      542.74,
      222.42
    ],
    "text": "They had four children. Subsequently, it is alleged that the Respondent contracted another",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      236.89,
      542.63,
      250.17
    ],
    "text": "marriage without the consent of the Appellant. Thereafter, the differences on the home front started",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      264.41,
      543.07,
      277.69
    ],
    "text": "culminating in the complete breakdown of the marriage. As such, the Appellant filed an application",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      291.91,
      368.4,
      305.19
    ],
    "text": "seeking a Faskh divorce before the Quazi Court of Panadura.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      327.66,
      542.76,
      340.94
    ],
    "text": "After the Respondent was noticed, he appeared before the Quazi and raised a preliminary objection",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      355.18,
      421.42,
      368.46
    ],
    "text": "before the said Quazi as to the jurisdiction of the Quazi on two grounds:",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      90.05,
      390.76,
      542.65,
      404.21
    ],
    "text": "i. The Appellant had commenced her residence in the local jurisdiction of the Quazi of",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      126.05,
      418.43,
      176.83,
      431.71
    ],
    "text": "Panadura.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      90.05,
      445.79,
      543.16,
      459.24
    ],
    "text": "ii. The Appellant had already instituted an application for a Faskh divorce before the",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      126.05,
      473.71,
      543.23,
      486.99
    ],
    "text": "Quazi of Gampaha and, after inquiry, the application for the Faskh divorce was refused.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      509.23,
      542.72,
      522.51
    ],
    "text": "Therefore, the learned Quazi of Panadura does not have the jurisdiction to entertain the application",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      536.98,
      542.68,
      550.26
    ],
    "text": "for Faskh divorce. However, the learned Quazi of Panadura overruled the said preliminary",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      564.48,
      543.01,
      577.76
    ],
